    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I'll look into this today. The thing is, this component worked perfectly\nwith no problems in 2.2.5 just never updated the search state. Every part\nof my app works minus this now. I was in a rush when I made this issue\nbecause I need it working next week. My bad on not giving you enough info!\nI'll post here later today.\nOn Thu, Feb 9, 2017 at 04:27 Marie-Laure Thuret <notifications@github.com>\nwrote:\n\n> Hi @zackify <https://github.com/zackify>, this shouldn't happen normally\n> as we perform a deepEqual when a component receive new props. So if the\n> props didn't changed, the onSearchStateChange shouldn't be trigger\n> infinitely.\n>\n> But sometimes depending on the upper component of the <InstantSearch/>\n> root component, those infinite loops can still happen, for example in the react-router\n> v3 recipe I had to implement the shouldComponentUpdate lifecycle method.\n>\n> Any chance you can provide a small sample to help us understand what's\n> happening with your use case? Maybe you can use this jsfiddle template\n> https://jsfiddle.net/h3nus3gg/?\n>\n> —\n> You are receiving this because you were mentioned.\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\n> <https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/1960#issuecomment-278589802>,\n> or mute the thread\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AAbacOYtIkF7bP8Y4_Zz4JAq6vNu6kuhks5ratv8gaJpZM4L7bq5>\n> .\n>\n",
