    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Here's the problem: I was doing:\r\n\r\n```\r\nif (this.state.lastPush && newPush - this.state.lastPush <= THRESHOLD) {\r\n      router.replace(nextSearchState ? `?${string}` : '')\r\n    } else {\r\n      router.push(nextSearchState ? `?${string}` : '')\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen set the search state from the location string:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n<InstantSearch\r\n          indexName={index}\r\n          searchState={qs.parse(location.search.substring(1)}\r\n      ....\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor some reason this causes an infinite render. I don't think it should. \r\n\r\nEdit: for some reason it just keeps being rendered, trying to debug it :/",
